{"commands": [{"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "\n%md-sandbox\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 0; padding-top: 9px;\">\n  <img src=\"https://databricks.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/db-academy-rgb-1200px.png\" alt=\"Databricks Learning\" style=\"width: 1200px\">\n</div>", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "b1636644-04d0-4548-ae58-4aa3af95eee2", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "593a055c-d284-4ae2-8767-dab2e6474f97", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 1, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md-sandbox\n<img src=\"https://files.training.databricks.com/images/Apache-Spark-Logo_TM_200px.png\" style=\"float: left: margin: 20px\"/>\n\n# Bronze To Silver - Investors 2\n\nAn investor's risk score indicates how much of a risk-taker he or she is based on historical data. Similarly, the asset risk score is assigned to a ticker showing how risky or volatile a stock is, on a scale of zero to ten.\n\nAll investors have a list of favorite stocks too. This list is a product of both behavioral and transactional data.\n\nIn this exercise we are going to combine the stocks and investors data by using the above mentioned information. Ultimately this is needed for the upstream marketing application designed for targeting investors.\n\n## In this exercise you will:\n* Practice how to `explode` rows \n* How to split strings with `split`\n* Practice how to join two DataFrames\n* Practice how to select columns after a join from one side of the join\n* Practice how to write to Delta format\n\n## Prerequisites\n* Web browser: **Chrome**\n* A cluster configured with **8 cores** and **DBR 7.0**", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "ffae7fe9-762c-439a-9d1b-63179b76d700", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "b3a0f2fd-d49b-414d-be30-e740defc5a4e", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 2, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md\n## ![Spark Logo Tiny](https://files.training.databricks.com/images/105/logo_spark_tiny.png) Classroom-Setup<br>\n\nFor each lesson to execute correctly, please make sure to run the **`Classroom-Setup`** cell at the start of each lesson (see the next cell) and the **`Classroom-Cleanup`** cell at the end of each lesson.", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "67b1a7b3-55a9-4f9b-9894-b67a7dbdf76a", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "00f41f20-d757-4689-a140-52e1be3fa14f", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 3, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%run ./Includes/PCF-08S-ClassroomSetup", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "71bac814-87bf-4b43-84d6-992450b0a7c8", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "03bdc40f-97f4-492f-9ce2-9410a10a9726", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 4, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md\n## ![Spark Logo Tiny](https://files.training.databricks.com/images/105/logo_spark_tiny.png) Steps to complete<br>\nImplement the **`challenge()`** function to achieve the following:\n\n- Read the investors from the **`investorsPath`** into a DataFrame.\n- Keep only the following fields: **`investor_id`**,  **`name`**,  **`credit_score`**,  **`risk_score`** and **`fav_stocks`**\n- Update the DataFrame using the column named **`fav_stocks`** so that there will be one single stock for each row for a given investor. Hint: convert it to a list and then _explode_.\n- Name this exploded field **`asset_id`** and drop the original **`fav_stocks`** field.\n- Read the assets from the **`assetsPath`** into a DataFrame.\n- Join the investors and the assets DataFrames using a left join.\n- Write the resulting DataFrame to **`targetDirectory`**.\n- Return the resulting DataFrame.\n\nThe resulting DataFrame's expected schema should look like this:\n\n|name|type|\n|---|---|\n|investor_id|LongType|\n|name|StringType|\n|credit_score|DoubleType|\n|risk_score|LongType|\n|asset_id|StringType|\n|asset_risk|IntegerType|", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "6e9ee9b6-a40b-4f8c-b5e8-78ae71a862cb", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "9af75eb7-1d14-4652-82fb-30620d3f4ee9", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 5, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "// TODO\n\ndef challenge(spark:org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession, investorsPath:String, assetsPath:String, targetDirectory:String) : DataFrame = {\n  \n  // Read the investors from the `investorsPath` into a DataFrame.\n  \n  // Keep only the following fields: `investor_id`,  `name`,  `credit_score`,  `risk_score` and `fav_stocks`.\n  \n  // Update the DataFrame using the column named `fav_stocks`, so that there will be one single stock for each row for a given investor. \n  // Hint: convert it to a list and then explode it. Name this exploded field `asset_id` and drop the original `fav_stocks` field.\n  \n  // Read the assets from the `assetsPath` into a DataFrame.\n  \n  // Join the investors and the assets DataFrames using a left join.\n  \n  // Write the resulting DataFrame to `targetDirectory` with overwrite mode and overwrite schema option\n  \n  // Return the resulting DataFrame.\n\n  return FILL_IN.DATAFRAME\n}\n\nval finalDF = challenge(spark, investorsPath, assetsPath, targetDirectory)\ndisplay(finalDF)", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "errorSummary": null, "finishTime": 0, "globalVars": {}, "guid": "ab294244-e09e-4adf-8c06-aeaf51edcccc", "height": "auto", "hideCommandCode": false, "hideCommandResult": false, "iPythonMetadata": null, "inputWidgets": {}, "latestUser": "", "latestUserId": null, "nuid": "1a80fa1b-2afc-4470-ba6f-d59ed75730df", "origId": 0, "parentHierarchy": [], "pivotAggregation": null, "pivotColumns": null, "position": 6, "results": null, "showCommandTitle": false, "startTime": 0, "state": "finished", "streamStates": {}, "submitTime": 0, "subtype": "command", "version": "CommandV1", "width": "auto", "workflows": [], "xColumns": null, "yColumns": null}, {"bindings": {}, "collapsed": false, "command": "%md\n<h2><img src=\"https://files.training.databricks.com/images/105/logo_spark_tiny.png\"> Reality Check</h2>\n\nRun the following cell to make sure you are on track:", "commandTitle": "", "commandType": "auto", "commandVersion": 0, "commentThread": [], "commentsVisible": false, "customPlotOptions": {}, "datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap": {}, "diffDeletes": [], "diffInserts": [], "displayType": "table", "error": null, "er